						               													<description>Initiation into the arcane arts takes place in the great tower of Rothra, amid libraries and archmages who guard apprentices as they experience the dangerous paths of mana. From time to time, one or another decides to test the ancient artifacts and thereby discover the power of the portals. Before being called summoners, they practice their mastery in combat, learning little by little about the infinite possibilities of each being that they will be able to call; these are the encounters that grow mages into future summoners.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1 vs 1 mode expansion for Invocaci&amp;#195;&amp;#179;n Fronteras.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Includes 2 promo cards:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Akari (41 - Air): Match your Reserve Mana to the player with the lowest Reserve Mana (minimum 1).&amp;#10;     Azael (60 - Air/Earth/Water/Fire): Your Power is equal to the lowest Power at this time, multiplied by 3.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Medium difficulty for new and old summoners.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this game mode the summoners prepare a deck each. Then they fight normally but the cards they use are the ones they set aside for themselves. It is a practical way to learn the cards and they generate a dynamic reminiscent of TCG or CCG games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Although 1 vs 1 is recommended, it is just as functional for more players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
